6.40	Lei_cha	Lei cha	Lei cha (Chinese: ; pinyin: léi chá; literally "pounded tea") is a Hakka tea-based beverage or gruel consisting of a mix of tea leaves and herbs that are ground or pounded together with various roasted nuts, seeds, and grains. The tea is drunk for breakfast or on cold winters as a tasty and healthy restorative. Lei cha is very popular in Taiwan, Southern China, Malaysia as well as any locales with a substantial Hakka diaspora population.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/Lei_cha.jpg/220px-Lei_cha.jpg
